HEADWORD: Inswept
<hw>In"swept`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Narrowed at the
forward end; -- said of an automobile frame when the side members are
closer together at the forward end than at the rear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intact</ent>⟦br⟧
